-- PRESS DIGEST- Financial Times - June 12
-- 
-- Wed Jun 11, 2014 08:51PM EDT
-- None



June 12 (Reuters) - The following are the top stories in the Financial Times. Reuters has not verified these stories and does not vouch for their accuracy.

Headlines  LAWSKY ASKS BNP TO REMOVE SENIOR ADVISER (http://link.reuters.com/haq99v)  SIEMENS AND MITSUBISHI EYE JOINT BID FOR ALSTOM'S ENERGY ASSETS (http://link.reuters.com/kaq99v)  AIRBUS SETBACK AS EMIRATES CANCELS $16 BLN ORDER FOR 70 A350 JETS (http://link.reuters.com/paq99v)  YANNIS STOURNARAS TO CONFRONT BAD LOANS AS GREEK BANK GOVERNOR (http://link.reuters.com/saq99v)  GOPRO SEEKS TO RAISE UP TO $427 MLN IN IPO (http://link.reuters.com/maq99v)  Overview  Benjamin Lawsky, New York's top banking regulator, is asking for the removal of a senior BNP Paribas <BNPP.PA> adviser as part of the settlement with U.S. authorities over sanction violations, according to a source familiar with the matter.  Siemens <SIEGn.DE> and Mitsubishi Heavy Industries <7011.T> are planning a joint bid for Alstom's <ALSO.PA> energy assets - the German and Japanese industrial conglomerates will be going up against General Electric <GE.N> $16.9 billion bid from last month.  Airbus <AIR.PA> took a blow on Wednesday after Dubai's Emirates Airline [EMIRA.UL] scrapped a $16 billion order for 70 of the European planemaker's new A350 passenger jets.  Greece confirmed that it has appointed Yannis Stournaras as its central bank's new governor one day after he stepped down as finance minister in a government reshuffle.